  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TB/MDR -TB Interventions among Afghan Refugees, Returnees and Mobile Populations in Afghanistan, the Islamic Republic of Iran and Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be implemented over three years in four border provinces of Afghanistan. This regional TB control project is envisioned to address some of the barriers of TB control and to build on and complement current activities in existing Global Fund grants and national programmes in Afghanistan, the Islamic Republic of Iran, and Pakistan. The overall objective is to increase TB case detection, treatment success rates and access to health services for Afghan refugees and returnees in the three countries. The project will complement the existing national programme in mapping cross-border mobility dynamics of returnees against health facilities and access to diagnosis; introducing the active case finding approach and building the capacity of stakeholders including the Health Cluster&#x2019;s service providers and the Ministry of Public Health.</narrative>
  </description>
